        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Rochester</placeName>
                <date>January 12 1857</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p>Dr Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">To reply to your favour of<lb/> the <date>31st</date> ult, I beg
                leave to hand<lb/> you our check on Shoe &amp; Leather Bank.<lb/> No 362. for.
                Twenty five 50/100 Dollars.<lb/> Which comprises the following items</p>
            <table cols="3" rows="4">
                <row>
                    <cell>to Occident 4 Vol.</cell>
                    <cell>$12.00</cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>from <persName>E Ellenheimer</persName> coll.</cell>
                    <cell>5.00</cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>“ <persName>L. Strassburger</persName></cell>
                    <cell>2.50</cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>“ the <persName>Revd. Dr Meyer</persName>.</cell>
                    <cell>6.00</cell>
                    <cell>$25.50</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>The Large Bible which you had charged<lb/> at Eight Dollars &amp; which at the
                time<lb/> of sending the Books you thought my Brother<lb/> would take is yet
                remaining with the other<lb/> Books, for he said, he had not agreed to<lb/> buy it,
                We shall retain the Books in<lb/> question until <persName>Dr Meyers</persName> will
                call for<lb/> them, as he probably will</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">M Seligman</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
